"v.妥协；危害 【英】 v. 妥协 (to settle by concessions)；危害(to lay open to danger or disrepute) 【考】 implacable : compromise / honest : swindle(难以抚慰的不会妥协 /诚实的不会诈骗)mediation : compromise / prosecution : conviction(调停为了达成和解/ 起诉为了定罪)反义词：intransigen t(不妥协的)-open to compromise(寻求和解 的) 【记】 com＋promise(保证) →相互保证→妥协,尤 其要注意'危害'一意 【例】 John felt compromised by what Jean had said about his friendship with the crimina v. 妥协(双方互相让步解决分歧的方法); 危害(名誉) 【例】Such conduct will compromise my reputation 如此举动将会损害我的名誉. I would rather die than compromise 我宁死不屈. 【记】com共同, promise发誓: 停战妥协就是两个国家共同发誓不打仗的产物. 【类】implacable: compromise = honest: swindle难以抚慰的不会妥协 = 诚实的不会诈骗mediation: compromise = prosecution: conviction调停为了和解 = 起诉为了定罪 【反】intransigent(adj 不妥协的)－open to compromise(可以和解的); polemical(adj 辩论法的; 好辩的)－compromising(adj 妥协的) 【记】com + promise 各方都允诺；妥协与折衷实际上各方受到损害的，因为都让步了 compromise (n.)  early 15c., ""a joint promise to abide by an arbiter's decision,"" from Middle French compromis (13c.), from Latin compromissus, past participle of compromittere ""to make a mutual promise"" (to abide by the arbiter's decision), from com- ""together"" (see com-) + promittere (see promise). The main modern sense of ""a coming to terms"" is from extension to the settlement itself (late 15c.). compromise (v.)  mid-15c., from compromise (n.). Related: Compromised; compromising."
